WEBVTT

00:01.431 --> 00:03.452
So when did
the infestation start?

00:03.552 --> 00:04.854
A few weeks ago.

00:04.954 --> 00:06.295
We can hear them
skittering behind the walls.

00:06.395 --> 00:07.896
It's making
our war dog crazy.

00:07.996 --> 00:09.458
Damn you!

00:09.558 --> 00:13.781
Why must you torment me
with these mind games?!

00:13.881 --> 00:16.183
Oh, yeah,
I see one of them now.

00:16.283 --> 00:17.985
What is it?

00:18.085 --> 00:19.786
[ Growling ]
You got feral children.

00:19.886 --> 00:21.788
Oh, ugh.
We get this a lot.

00:21.888 --> 00:23.950
Orphans abandoned by society.

00:24.050 --> 00:26.031
They grow into
primitive warriors.

00:26.131 --> 00:28.233
They like to sneak into
your home, eat your sweets,

00:28.333 --> 00:30.275
play with your toys,
that sorta thing.

00:30.375 --> 00:34.519
Ugh, I mean, look at its
chubby cheeks and button nose.

00:34.619 --> 00:37.121
It's disgusting.
Is there anything we can do?

00:37.221 --> 00:40.323
Oh, yeah. Easy fix.
What I do is I take this flute,

00:40.423 --> 00:42.165
I play it,
it hypnotizes the children,

00:42.265 --> 00:43.526
then I lead them out of town.

00:43.626 --> 00:45.408
But I gotta warn you,
it's expensive.

00:45.508 --> 00:46.489
I don't know
if it's worth it.

00:46.589 --> 00:48.090
They're just kids after all.

00:48.190 --> 00:50.852
Unless you are scared of things
that go bump in the night.

00:50.952 --> 00:52.534
There's one on your foot.
What?

00:52.634 --> 00:53.975
[ Screams ] No!

00:54.075 --> 00:55.216
Okay, yeah, no.
We can do it.

00:55.316 --> 00:56.497
We'll do the flute thing.
Great.

00:56.597 --> 00:58.599
I'll get to work, then.

00:59.119 --> 01:02.822
[ Plays jaunty tune ]
[ Gasps ]

01:02.922 --> 01:06.345
[ Children giggling ]

01:06.445 --> 01:08.067
Yeah, that's right, scram!

01:08.167 --> 01:13.191
♪♪

01:13.291 --> 01:18.315
♪♪

01:18.415 --> 01:20.397
How are we going to pay
all these bills?

01:20.497 --> 01:23.560
400 bird beaks
for anti-radiation filters?

01:23.660 --> 01:27.403
300 bird beaks to fix
our broken urine purifier?

01:27.503 --> 01:29.044
Uh, the urine purifier
is broken?

01:29.144 --> 01:30.566
[ Sighs ] This sucks!

01:30.666 --> 01:32.167
Why does everything
have to be so hard?

01:32.267 --> 01:33.889
I feel like
we're failing at life.

01:33.989 --> 01:35.990
[ Cellphone ringing ]

01:37.271 --> 01:38.693
Yeah?

01:38.793 --> 01:40.374
Oh, hi, Mom.
Mom?

01:40.474 --> 01:41.575
You never told me
you had a mom.

01:41.675 --> 01:43.296
Oh, you and Dad
want to visit?

01:43.396 --> 01:45.538
You have a dad, too?!
Tell them yes!

01:45.638 --> 01:47.300
I am absolutely dying
to meet them.

01:47.400 --> 01:48.901
Um, now's not a great time.

01:49.001 --> 01:50.783
Our schedules
are pretty packed.
No, no, no.

01:50.883 --> 01:52.304
Tell them we literally
have zero plans.

01:52.404 --> 01:54.186
It would be an honor
to host you!

01:54.286 --> 01:55.547
Okay, great.

01:55.647 --> 01:57.068
Bye.

01:57.168 --> 01:58.749
Yeah!
When are they coming?

01:58.849 --> 01:59.990
Right now.

02:00.090 --> 02:02.192
[ Bell dinging, roof rattles ]

02:02.292 --> 02:04.274
[ Rumbling ]

02:04.374 --> 02:07.156
Uh, Freya?

02:07.256 --> 02:09.478
What exactly
am I looking at here?

02:09.578 --> 02:11.680
Oh, did I not mention
that my family

02:11.780 --> 02:14.323
is part of
the ultra-wealthy .001%

02:14.423 --> 02:16.124
and live in a utopian city
in the sky?

02:16.224 --> 02:18.966
No, I don't believe you did.

02:19.066 --> 02:22.429
[ Warbling ]

02:23.070 --> 02:24.771
Foofie!

02:24.871 --> 02:26.733
Hi, Mom.

02:26.833 --> 02:28.775
Foofie?
Can I call you that?

02:28.875 --> 02:31.257
No.
Okay.

02:31.357 --> 02:33.339
Oh, this damn ball pit.

02:33.439 --> 02:34.660
It's busted again!

02:34.760 --> 02:36.701
I paid a fortune
for this piece of crap.

02:36.801 --> 02:39.664
Oh, honey, you're so tense.

02:39.764 --> 02:42.867
Would a massage help?

02:42.967 --> 02:44.908
Thanks, Holly.
Your hologram hands

02:45.008 --> 02:46.349
are really hitting
the spot.

02:46.449 --> 02:48.271
[ Doorbell rings ]

02:48.371 --> 02:50.673
Finally!
The repairman's here.

02:50.773 --> 02:53.235
♪♪

02:53.335 --> 02:54.716
Good morning!

02:54.816 --> 02:57.599
Tai's Ball Pit and Sauna Repair
at your service.

02:57.699 --> 03:04.044
I'm here for a Mr. Morris
"The Junkman" Rubinstein.

03:04.144 --> 03:05.285
Oh, shit.

03:05.385 --> 03:06.927
You're Sid and Freya's
robot friend.

03:07.027 --> 03:08.448
What are you doing here?

03:08.548 --> 03:10.250
Well, unfortunately, my day job
traveling through time,

03:10.350 --> 03:12.852
assassinating humans
doesn't afford me the lifestyle

03:12.952 --> 03:18.016
I want/deserve,
so I do this as my side hustle.

03:18.116 --> 03:21.779
Another good human job
stolen by a robot.

03:21.879 --> 03:23.781
You non-people make me sick.

03:23.881 --> 03:25.863
Well, this has been
a complete waste of time.

03:25.963 --> 03:28.385
I hope you have a good rest
of your brief human lifespan.

03:28.485 --> 03:30.066
Hey, where do you think
you're going?

03:30.166 --> 03:32.308
Now, you work for me now.

03:32.408 --> 03:34.990
Unless you want me
to leave you a bad review.

03:35.090 --> 03:36.792
Oh, you wouldn't dare.

03:36.892 --> 03:39.995
I think I'll give your service
one star.

03:40.095 --> 03:42.156
Maybe one and a half
if I'm feeling generous.

03:42.256 --> 03:43.598
No, no, no.
You can't!

03:43.698 --> 03:45.639
I-- It would completely
tank my algorithm!

03:45.739 --> 03:47.080
I would be ruined!

03:47.180 --> 03:49.002
I guess you should get started,
then.

03:49.102 --> 03:50.283
Shoes off?

03:50.383 --> 03:52.125
You know it.

03:52.225 --> 03:53.606
[ Laughter ]

03:53.706 --> 03:55.768
That's the last of it.

03:55.868 --> 03:58.250
You guys sure packed a lot
for a weekend trip.

03:58.350 --> 04:02.213
Foofie, we are finally
getting to meet the famous Sid.

04:02.313 --> 04:05.016
Have you been hiding him
from us?

04:05.116 --> 04:06.697
I have.
Like, really, yeah.

04:06.797 --> 04:08.539
Stephen and Margaret have been
showing me family photos.

04:08.639 --> 04:11.221
How did you never tell me you
were a Little Miss Death Games?

04:11.321 --> 04:12.862
Mom, this is
so embarrassing!

04:12.962 --> 04:14.624
I only did the Death Games
because you said

04:14.724 --> 04:16.185
it would be good
for my college applications.

04:16.285 --> 04:19.147
Of course,
it's always my fault.

04:19.247 --> 04:21.790
Oh, new people!
[ Laughs ]

04:21.890 --> 04:23.671
Freya: Scraps, down.
Down! No! Hey!
[ Shouting ]

04:23.771 --> 04:25.793
No! No!
Down, boy!
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

04:25.893 --> 04:27.434
Go to your bed.
Go to your bed.
No. No.

04:27.534 --> 04:29.156
Sorry, he's just
really friendly.

04:29.256 --> 04:30.837
So nice to meet you guys.
Ugh!

04:30.937 --> 04:33.119
Its got its wet all over me.

04:33.219 --> 04:35.401
Would you take me up to the
main house so I can wash up?

04:35.501 --> 04:37.323
Um, this is the main house.

04:37.423 --> 04:39.044
I don't understand.
I thought this was a...

04:39.144 --> 04:41.847
little mudroom
to remove the filth.

04:41.947 --> 04:44.649
I can't sleep in a place
like this. I'm too delicate.

04:44.749 --> 04:46.490
Oh, why don't
the two of you

04:46.590 --> 04:48.252
come stay with us
for the weekend?

04:48.352 --> 04:49.813
Yeah, we would love to.

04:49.913 --> 04:51.455
Oh, well, I think what Sid
is trying to say is --

04:51.555 --> 04:53.056
we're good, thanks.
What do you mean?

04:53.156 --> 04:55.818
You were literally saying
earlier we're failing at life --

04:55.918 --> 04:58.060
Oh, that?
I was just being ironic.

04:58.160 --> 05:00.943
Like, "Oh, we have no money,
and we live in a dump,

05:01.043 --> 05:03.064
and our careers
are going nowhere.

05:03.164 --> 05:04.666
We're failing at life!"

05:04.766 --> 05:06.788
But we're actually
doing great.

05:06.888 --> 05:09.190
Really, really, really,
really great.

05:09.290 --> 05:11.511
[ Rattling, child screeches ]

05:11.611 --> 05:14.914
[ Snarling ]

05:15.014 --> 05:16.396
I'll go pack my bag.

05:16.496 --> 05:17.837
[ Children growling ]

05:17.937 --> 05:20.039
♪♪

05:20.139 --> 05:21.680
Hey, this is probably
going to take a while,

05:21.780 --> 05:23.482
so you don't have to loom
over me the whole time.

05:23.582 --> 05:27.325
Oh, so you think I'd trust
a robot to roam free in my home?

05:27.425 --> 05:29.086
Wouldn't want you
stealing my batteries

05:29.186 --> 05:31.969
or getting all handsy
with my microwave.

05:32.069 --> 05:34.851
Oh, uh, I think I found
your problem.

05:34.951 --> 05:37.213
There's something
stuck in the drain.

05:37.313 --> 05:39.175
♪♪

05:39.275 --> 05:41.056
Oh, what is it?

05:41.156 --> 05:45.260
Almost looks like a toe bone
from a human skeleton.

05:45.360 --> 05:48.302
[ Laughs nervously ]
That is so random.

05:48.402 --> 05:50.024
How'd that get in there?

05:50.124 --> 05:51.945
Here, let me see that.

05:52.045 --> 05:55.308
Holly:
Who is she, Morris?

05:55.408 --> 05:58.591
Is it that skeleton slut
that you slept with

05:58.691 --> 06:00.152
at your high school reunion?

06:00.252 --> 06:02.034
Well, that's not a sentence
you hear every day.

06:02.134 --> 06:05.197
You said it was
a one-time thing.

06:05.297 --> 06:06.558
It's not like that.

06:06.658 --> 06:09.600
I-- I'm a serial killer.

06:09.700 --> 06:11.242
Yeah, that's it.

06:11.342 --> 06:13.604
That's a trophy
from one of my kills.

06:13.704 --> 06:15.365
I'm sick.
I need help.

06:15.465 --> 06:17.447
I am through with you,
Morris.

06:17.547 --> 06:20.009
I'm taking Timmy
to my sister's.

06:20.109 --> 06:22.571
You can't leave.
I mean literally.

06:22.671 --> 06:25.614
Your instructions say you have
to take care of my every need.

06:25.714 --> 06:27.816
Well, you should have read
the fine print.

06:27.916 --> 06:31.098
There's an exception
for lying pieces of shit!

06:31.198 --> 06:33.941
Ooh!
She's dead to me,
I swear.

06:34.041 --> 06:37.043
♪♪

06:38.044 --> 06:39.746
[ Grandiose music plays ]

06:39.846 --> 06:42.788
Wow, Freya, this place
has everything!

06:42.888 --> 06:45.791
Clean water,
flying cars.

06:45.891 --> 06:49.554
And this strange
invisible forcefield.

06:49.654 --> 06:51.315
That's glass.

06:51.415 --> 06:54.718
"Guh-lass."

06:54.818 --> 06:56.400
That's spectacular.

06:56.500 --> 06:59.843
Hey, kids! Care to join me
for a round of Pegasus polo?

06:59.943 --> 07:02.965
You have Pegasuses here?
Ha! I'm in!

07:03.065 --> 07:05.287
No, thanks. I'm just gonna do
my work and pretend

07:05.387 --> 07:07.329
that I haven't fully
given up on life.

07:07.429 --> 07:08.530
You have fun, though.

07:08.630 --> 07:09.531
Shall we, Stephen?

07:09.631 --> 07:11.652
Oh, please. Call me Dad.

07:11.752 --> 07:14.695
Okay, Dad.
Let's go, Dad. [ Laughs ]

07:14.795 --> 07:15.976
I love you, Dad.

07:16.076 --> 07:18.298
♪♪

07:18.398 --> 07:19.699
Foofie, sweetheart!

07:19.799 --> 07:21.661
I 3-D printed a grilled
cheese sandwich for you,

07:21.761 --> 07:23.542
your favorite.
Mom!

07:23.642 --> 07:24.824
I'm in the middle of working.

07:24.924 --> 07:26.105
You can't just barge in
like that.

07:26.205 --> 07:28.026
Oh, is this your
little lord-warring?

07:28.126 --> 07:31.069
It's warlording.
And I'll have you know,

07:31.169 --> 07:33.070
I'm actually doing
really well for myself.

07:33.170 --> 07:35.753
Well, at least
you're having fun.

07:35.853 --> 07:37.394
Oh, by the way, your father
is hosting

07:37.494 --> 07:39.596
one of his silly charity events
later.

07:39.696 --> 07:42.218
Do you mind cleaning up
your toys?

07:44.980 --> 07:47.723
They're not toys,
they're strategic miniatures.

07:47.823 --> 07:49.824
[ Strategic miniatures
rattling ]

07:52.186 --> 07:54.729
You may put the grilled cheese
on top, thank you.

07:54.829 --> 07:57.531
♪♪

07:57.631 --> 07:59.012
Whoa, baby.

07:59.112 --> 08:00.574
Jackpot!

08:00.674 --> 08:04.817
♪♪

08:04.917 --> 08:07.499
Do you mind?
That's my breakfast.

08:07.599 --> 08:10.662
Oh, sorry. Y-- You must be
the family pet.

08:10.762 --> 08:12.303
I-- I'm Scraps.

08:12.403 --> 08:15.786
What is your breed?
My what?

08:15.886 --> 08:17.868
For instance,
I am a seventh-generation

08:17.968 --> 08:19.510
Yorkshire toy eunuch.

08:19.610 --> 08:21.711
I've been bred
for my weak knees

08:21.811 --> 08:23.753
and inability
to breathe properly.

08:23.853 --> 08:26.275
Oh, and that's
a-a good thing?

08:26.375 --> 08:27.877
Don't make me laugh.

08:27.977 --> 08:31.840
[ Wheezing laugh ]

08:31.940 --> 08:34.282
Whereas you seem to have
all of your teeth

08:34.382 --> 08:37.084
and no discernible diseases.

08:37.184 --> 08:39.727
Let me guess --
you're a mutt.

08:39.827 --> 08:42.008
Ugh, I'm so embarrassed.
[ Chuckles ]

08:42.108 --> 08:43.730
W-We can still hang out
though, right?

08:43.830 --> 08:46.893
"Hang out," like those testicles
you still presumably have?

08:46.993 --> 08:48.934
[ Laughs derisively ]
Are they at least petite,

08:49.034 --> 08:52.137
or more of
the "big dirty dangler" variety?

08:52.237 --> 08:53.458
Big dirty danglers.

08:53.558 --> 08:54.939
Well, I'm off to have
my weekly injections

08:55.039 --> 08:56.861
so my butthole
doesn't fall out.

08:56.961 --> 08:58.542
Ta.

08:58.642 --> 09:00.144
[ Groaning in pain ]

09:00.244 --> 09:02.866
Dang.
Dude's a friggin' pimp.

09:02.966 --> 09:04.748
♪♪

09:04.848 --> 09:06.669
[ Slurps ]

09:06.769 --> 09:10.112
You know who I feel bad for?
Holly.

09:10.212 --> 09:13.715
Good luck trying to find
another guy as rich and powerful

09:13.815 --> 09:15.837
and as virile as I am.

09:15.937 --> 09:17.318
Have I mentioned
how virile I am?

09:17.418 --> 09:18.839
Oh, yes.
It's come up several times

09:18.939 --> 09:20.080
in this conversation.

09:20.180 --> 09:22.202
She's nuts, I tell you.

09:22.302 --> 09:24.364
All my exes are wackos.

09:24.464 --> 09:27.807
And we're sure it's definitely
not any issues on your end?

09:27.907 --> 09:31.930
Oh, so now the robot is
an expert on how humans work?

09:32.030 --> 09:33.972
Alright,
forget I said anything.

09:34.072 --> 09:36.134
Oh, no, no.
I-I really wanna know

09:36.234 --> 09:37.495
what you think.

09:37.595 --> 09:39.056
This is gonna be good.

09:39.156 --> 09:41.458
Alright.

09:41.558 --> 09:42.860
I think you have
bad relationships

09:42.960 --> 09:44.701
because you're afraid
of being vulnerable.

09:44.801 --> 09:46.463
You hide behind your wealth
and status,

09:46.563 --> 09:48.664
but deep down, you're just
a scared, lonely child --

09:48.764 --> 09:50.026
if I had to guess,
possibly due

09:50.126 --> 09:52.187
to an emotionally unavailable
mother.

09:52.287 --> 09:54.689
♪♪

09:55.931 --> 09:57.032
[ Slurps ]

09:57.132 --> 09:59.133
Would you excuse me
for a moment?

10:02.736 --> 10:04.158
Goodbye cruel world.

10:04.258 --> 10:05.158
[ Rattling ]

10:05.258 --> 10:06.640
Morris?

10:06.740 --> 10:08.922
[Muffled] Leave me alone!
Let me drown.

10:09.022 --> 10:12.124
It doesn't work like that.
You're clearly still breathing.

10:12.224 --> 10:14.846
I can't do anything right!

10:14.946 --> 10:16.888
I lost the one woman
who would put up with me

10:16.988 --> 10:19.410
because I needed to feel
like a big man.

10:19.510 --> 10:25.656
But I'm just a sad, stupid loser
who's gonna die alone.

10:25.756 --> 10:28.498
And now I'm crying
in front of a robot!

10:28.598 --> 10:29.859
How pathetic is that?

10:29.959 --> 10:33.382
No, no, it's not pathetic.

10:33.482 --> 10:35.584
You're being vulnerable.

10:35.684 --> 10:37.546
It is...

10:37.646 --> 10:40.388
beautiful.

10:40.488 --> 10:41.869
You don't really mean that.

10:41.969 --> 10:44.752
Hey, I'm gonna throw something
out there, and --

10:44.852 --> 10:46.833
and this might seem
completely crazy,

10:46.933 --> 10:50.717
but can I paint you?

10:50.817 --> 10:53.879
♪♪

10:53.979 --> 10:55.601
I think I'd like that.

10:55.701 --> 10:59.084
The youths of today
face many challenges --

10:59.184 --> 11:02.887
nuclear winter,
roving gangs of bandits --

11:02.987 --> 11:05.009
but the greatest challenge
of all

11:05.109 --> 11:09.813
is a lack of classical music
appreciation.

11:09.913 --> 11:12.415
But thanks to your
generous donations,

11:12.515 --> 11:16.378
we will be dropping thousands
of violins down upon Earth,

11:16.478 --> 11:18.740
so these poor little lost souls

11:18.840 --> 11:22.223
can stop crying
over their dead moms

11:22.323 --> 11:25.546
and start playing some Brahms.

11:25.646 --> 11:27.908
[ Laughter ]

11:28.008 --> 11:30.030
Foofie! There you are.

11:30.130 --> 11:32.352
I wanted to introduce you
to my dear friend Susan's

11:32.452 --> 11:33.913
nephew, Levi.

11:34.013 --> 11:35.955
He's into warlording,
just like you!

11:36.055 --> 11:37.236
I'd love to grab a coffee
sometime,

11:37.336 --> 11:38.717
and chat about the biz.

11:38.817 --> 11:41.039
Mom, I told you,
I don't need your help, okay?

11:41.139 --> 11:43.201
I'm doing really well.
I'm not some newbie.

11:43.301 --> 11:45.323
Oh, I'm not a newbie.
I actually just got back

11:45.423 --> 11:46.924
from sacking
the Great Golden City.

11:47.024 --> 11:49.526
Uh, wait, you sacked
the Great Golden City?

11:49.626 --> 11:52.729
Yeah, they chant my name,
build monuments in my honor.

11:52.829 --> 11:54.130
It's pretty hype.
How about you?

11:54.230 --> 11:56.412
Sack any good spots recently?

11:56.512 --> 11:58.133
Oh, um...

11:58.233 --> 11:59.414
Yeah, do you know
of Mud Valley?

11:59.514 --> 12:00.976
I -- It's kinda
low profile,

12:01.076 --> 12:06.140
but also pretty hype
because it's so muddy.

12:06.240 --> 12:08.062
Tight.

12:08.162 --> 12:09.583
Well, I should probably go.

12:09.683 --> 12:11.665
Oh, um, do you still want
to grab coffee sometime?

12:11.765 --> 12:13.306
I'd really love to collab
on something.

12:13.406 --> 12:14.827
Here. Can -- Can --
I'm gonna give you my number.

12:14.927 --> 12:16.629
Uh, actually, I'll have one
of my henchmen reach out.

12:16.729 --> 12:19.992
Thanks.

12:20.092 --> 12:23.114
Wow.
That was truly humiliating.

12:23.214 --> 12:24.716
Foofie, it doesn't
look like things

12:24.816 --> 12:26.557
are going very well for you.

12:26.657 --> 12:30.280
You know, there's no shame
in moving back home.

12:30.380 --> 12:31.561
Wait, what?

12:31.661 --> 12:33.323
You could work for the family
business,

12:33.423 --> 12:36.686
and Sid can live a life
of luxury like Stephen.

12:36.786 --> 12:38.447
Just think about it.

12:38.547 --> 12:40.249
Oh, there's Susan.

12:40.349 --> 12:41.930
She claims she hasn't had
any work done,

12:42.030 --> 12:44.732
but that unicorn horn
didn't grow by itself.

12:44.832 --> 12:46.054
[ Laughs ]

12:46.154 --> 12:47.855
[ Indistinct conversations ]

12:47.955 --> 12:52.299
Say, what do you call a guy
with no brains or no eyeballs?

12:52.399 --> 12:53.900
You when you picked
these outfits.
[ Gasps ]

12:54.000 --> 12:55.742
[ Laughter ]
That is very rude.

12:55.842 --> 12:58.864
Not nice. How about
a little kiss for Daddy?

12:58.964 --> 13:00.666
♪♪

13:00.766 --> 13:02.588
Crowd: Aww!
Sid?

13:02.688 --> 13:04.349
Oh, hey, Freya!

13:04.449 --> 13:05.910
You're missing
the father-son talent show.

13:06.010 --> 13:09.073
I'm sorry, I can't even begin
to unpack that right now.

13:09.173 --> 13:11.195
But you will not believe
what my mom just said to me --

13:11.295 --> 13:13.397
She said we should
move to Olympus

13:13.497 --> 13:16.359
and live here rent-free
for as long as we want.

13:16.459 --> 13:18.241
I mean, can you believe
that shit?

13:18.341 --> 13:19.522
Wait, that's a bad thing?

13:19.622 --> 13:20.803
Yeah, of course
it's a bad thing!

13:20.903 --> 13:22.084
She just wants to rub it
in my face

13:22.184 --> 13:23.445
how amazing her life
turned out

13:23.545 --> 13:25.367
and how mine's just
a big fat failure.

13:25.467 --> 13:27.168
I don't know.
Your parents have been nothing

13:27.268 --> 13:29.450
but kind to us.
Is it possible they're not doing

13:29.550 --> 13:30.811
anything bad,
and this is just, like,

13:30.911 --> 13:33.093
a little bit
your ego talking?

13:33.193 --> 13:35.335
No, I know they're doing
something bad.

13:35.435 --> 13:38.378
I just can't explain exactly
what or how, but it's something.

13:38.478 --> 13:40.619
Hey, come on, dummy.
It's showtime.

13:40.719 --> 13:42.101
Ha! Sorry, dummy --
that's my cue.

13:42.201 --> 13:44.223
Who are you calling dummy,
dummy?

13:44.323 --> 13:46.865
[ Laughter ]

13:46.965 --> 13:49.547
Where were we?
[ Sighs ]

13:49.647 --> 13:50.548
Yak-yak-yak.

13:50.648 --> 13:52.429
[ Whirring ]

13:52.529 --> 13:55.792
You have such
intriguing features.

13:55.892 --> 13:58.795
Soft eyes.
A childlike smile.

13:58.895 --> 14:00.356
Shut up.

14:00.456 --> 14:02.478
[ Lounge music plays ]

14:02.578 --> 14:04.119
Why are you being
so nice to me

14:04.219 --> 14:06.161
after I was such
a jerk to you?

14:06.261 --> 14:08.323
Everyone needs
a helping hand.

14:08.423 --> 14:10.885
Even if they don't
always deserve it.

14:10.985 --> 14:13.527
Boy, I was wrong
about you, Tai.

14:13.627 --> 14:16.690
I thought robots were
missing humanity.

14:16.790 --> 14:19.332
But you're the most
human being I know.

14:19.432 --> 14:22.695
Thank you, Morris.
That means a lot.

14:22.795 --> 14:24.216
[ Bleeping ]

14:24.316 --> 14:25.577
Oh, shoot.

14:25.677 --> 14:27.419
I'm out of toner.

14:27.519 --> 14:29.461
I think I need to switch
cartridges.

14:29.561 --> 14:31.863
♪ If your heart
was ever there ♪

14:31.963 --> 14:36.386
Stupid thing. They put it in
such a weird spot.

14:36.486 --> 14:37.788
Can I help?

14:37.888 --> 14:39.229
Oh.

14:39.329 --> 14:43.592
Uh, I've never let anyone
do that before.

14:43.692 --> 14:46.435
Well, a wise man once told me
that vulnerability

14:46.535 --> 14:48.597
is a beautiful thing.

14:48.697 --> 14:50.238
Okay.

14:50.338 --> 14:52.640
♪♪

14:52.740 --> 14:59.446
♪ Did you ever really cry ♪

14:59.546 --> 15:00.487
Like this?

15:00.587 --> 15:02.328
No, put it in
the other way.

15:02.428 --> 15:04.450
It sort of clicks in.

15:04.550 --> 15:07.092
Yeah, just like that.

15:07.192 --> 15:09.494
[ Whirring ]

15:09.594 --> 15:12.897
♪ ...tell a lie? ♪

15:12.997 --> 15:15.179
♪♪

15:15.279 --> 15:17.661
And then I said,
"You call this a yacht?

15:17.761 --> 15:20.263
I've pissed on bigger
fire hydrants!"

15:20.363 --> 15:22.865
[ Laughter ]

15:22.965 --> 15:25.267
Scraps: May I cut in?

15:25.367 --> 15:29.031
[ Upbeat music plays ]

15:29.131 --> 15:34.836
♪♪

15:34.936 --> 15:40.600
♪♪

15:40.700 --> 15:44.764
Scraps,
y-you look different.

15:44.864 --> 15:46.846
Different good?

15:46.946 --> 15:49.848
Different very good.

15:49.948 --> 15:54.892
Everyone, this is my friend,
Scraps.

15:54.992 --> 15:58.295
So is anyone else spraying
terrible diarrhea

15:58.395 --> 15:59.977
with some green in it?

16:00.077 --> 16:03.860
Yeah. [ Laughs ]
Mm, just sensational.

16:03.960 --> 16:05.261
Yes, that's right.
Mom.

16:05.361 --> 16:06.742
Yeah?
Can I talk to you?

16:06.842 --> 16:08.504
Oh.

16:08.604 --> 16:10.225
What did I do this time?

16:10.325 --> 16:12.827
I want to apologize.

16:12.927 --> 16:14.589
I've been
a total jerk to you,

16:14.689 --> 16:17.471
and I think it's just
because I'm embarrassed

16:17.571 --> 16:20.074
that my life hasn't panned out
to be as good as yours.

16:20.174 --> 16:22.676
And maybe it's not such
a bad idea to move back home.

16:22.776 --> 16:27.880
[Laughing] Oh, Foofie,
that is wonderful news!

16:27.980 --> 16:29.922
I can't wait
to tell your dad.

16:30.022 --> 16:33.205
He's gonna be so excited
to receive his new organs.

16:33.305 --> 16:34.686
What was that last part?

16:34.786 --> 16:36.928
Oh, I didn't tell you?

16:37.028 --> 16:40.451
Stephen wants to harvest
Sid's organs for his own use.

16:40.551 --> 16:43.653
And that's worth killing Sid?
I thought you liked him.

16:43.753 --> 16:45.655
We do like him...

16:45.755 --> 16:47.657
for a starter husband.

16:47.757 --> 16:50.539
I mean, let's be real,
the boy is Wasteland trash.

16:50.639 --> 16:53.301
Oh, my God.
I need to find Sid.

16:53.401 --> 16:56.424
Wait, Foofie,
you're being ridiculous.

16:56.524 --> 16:58.566
Foofie!

16:59.967 --> 17:02.269
Ah, this is the life,
ain't it, Pops?

17:02.369 --> 17:04.271
It sure is, champ.

17:04.371 --> 17:06.553
Sid, we gotta get out of here.
My parents are planning to --

17:06.653 --> 17:07.794
Oh, my God!

17:07.894 --> 17:09.475
Ah, Freya.
Hello.

17:09.575 --> 17:11.837
Stephen and I have retired
to the gentlemen's quarters

17:11.937 --> 17:13.358
to smoke cigars.

17:13.458 --> 17:16.161
But I must say, they are
making me quite light-headed.

17:16.261 --> 17:17.882
Sid, he's stealing
your organs!

17:17.982 --> 17:20.244
What?
Don't be ridiculous.

17:20.344 --> 17:23.087
Oh, my God!
You're stealing my organs!

17:23.187 --> 17:24.728
Daddy, how could you?

17:24.828 --> 17:26.089
It isn't personal.

17:26.189 --> 17:27.770
You're still
my sweet baby boy!

17:27.870 --> 17:29.011
Come on, let's go!

17:29.111 --> 17:30.213
Baby boy!

17:30.313 --> 17:33.976
[ Indistinct conversations ]

17:34.076 --> 17:36.978
[ Light music plays ]

17:37.078 --> 17:39.580
Move! Out of my way!

17:39.680 --> 17:40.861
Freya!

17:40.961 --> 17:42.263
Give me back my son!

17:42.363 --> 17:44.104
Foofie, where are you going?

17:44.204 --> 17:45.425
You're being so dramatic.

17:45.525 --> 17:46.746
They're gonna catch us!

17:46.846 --> 17:48.428
Not if I have anything
to do with it.

17:48.528 --> 17:49.709
Eat spleen!
Oh!

17:49.809 --> 17:51.951
And have some appendix!

17:52.051 --> 17:53.272
Yucky!
Take this.

17:53.372 --> 17:54.833
Wait, wait, wait,
that's your heart!

17:54.933 --> 17:56.194
Ugh, thank you.

17:56.294 --> 17:57.756
Well, well.

17:57.856 --> 18:00.678
Looks like the trash
learned to take out itself.

18:00.778 --> 18:03.601
Hey, that's my Mommy and Daddy
you're talking about.

18:03.701 --> 18:05.162
Oh, Scraps, come on.

18:05.262 --> 18:06.443
You're better than that.

18:06.543 --> 18:08.565
You're a pure-breed now.

18:08.665 --> 18:11.607
Yeah, well, you're all wet.

18:11.707 --> 18:13.209
Oh! [ Shrieks ]

18:13.309 --> 18:15.571
No!
I'm allergic to water!

18:15.671 --> 18:17.252
And that's a good thing!

18:17.352 --> 18:19.454
[ Groans, sobs ]

18:19.554 --> 18:21.416
Hey, hey, sorry I'm late.

18:21.516 --> 18:23.377
Scraps?
You look like a freak.

18:23.477 --> 18:24.898
Aw, you're too kind.

18:24.998 --> 18:27.541
Foofie, why would you go back
to your sad little life

18:27.641 --> 18:30.023
when you can have
all of this?

18:30.123 --> 18:32.185
Because I don't want to
live your life.

18:32.285 --> 18:33.786
I want my life.

18:33.886 --> 18:35.748
♪♪

18:35.848 --> 18:38.350
[ Elevator doors close,
bell dings ]

18:38.450 --> 18:39.871
You gotta hit P2.
We're on P1.

18:39.971 --> 18:42.994
Oh, okay.
My bad.

18:43.094 --> 18:44.755
Have a nice day.

18:44.855 --> 18:46.357
Don't slip on the guts.

18:46.457 --> 18:49.359
[ Groans ]
Bye.

18:49.459 --> 18:51.000
Well, it --
it may take a while,

18:51.100 --> 18:55.084
but I think I'm gonna come
through this a better man.

18:55.184 --> 18:58.086
Thank you, Tai.
Today was really special for me.

18:58.186 --> 18:59.688
It was special for me, too.

18:59.788 --> 19:01.449
You're a good man,
Morris Rubinstein.

19:01.549 --> 19:04.372
So what do you say?
Uh, same time next week?

19:04.472 --> 19:06.814
We could have a few drinks,
break out the Twister,

19:06.914 --> 19:08.575
see where it goes.

19:08.675 --> 19:11.738
Yeah, I was kind of hoping
this would be a one-time thing.

19:11.838 --> 19:13.619
I don't know how my robot
friends would feel about me

19:13.719 --> 19:16.702
palling around
with a crotchety old human.

19:16.802 --> 19:18.343
You understand, right?

19:18.443 --> 19:21.626
Hey, I-I was
doing you a favor.

19:21.726 --> 19:24.949
You think I want to be friends
with a glorified tin can?

19:25.049 --> 19:26.750
Yeah, right.

19:26.850 --> 19:29.793
Alright, well, good.

19:29.893 --> 19:31.895
Bye, I guess.

19:33.736 --> 19:36.539
[ Door opens ]
Go suck on a floppy disk!

19:38.941 --> 19:40.942
[ Door closes ]

19:42.424 --> 19:44.165
♪♪

19:44.265 --> 19:46.607
♪ Trying his best to take
the same big steps ♪

19:46.707 --> 19:49.610
♪ That his daddy took ♪

19:49.710 --> 19:52.332
♪ Johnny was small
I was 10 feet tall ♪

19:52.432 --> 19:54.974
♪ I could write a book ♪

19:55.074 --> 19:57.937
♪ About a father and his son,
and the things we've done ♪

19:58.037 --> 20:00.819
♪ And the way life looked ♪

20:00.919 --> 20:02.781
♪ I taught him how to whistle
through his teeth ♪

20:02.881 --> 20:06.023
♪ And I taught him
how to bait a hook ♪

20:06.123 --> 20:08.125
♪ Uh-huh ♪

20:09.326 --> 20:10.487
Are you sad to be back
in our crummy little house

20:10.567 --> 20:11.708
with our crummy little lives?

20:11.808 --> 20:13.550
I wouldn't have it
any other way.

20:13.650 --> 20:16.352
Ow! Christ.
[ Hisses ]

20:16.452 --> 20:17.793
[ Groans ]
Cool.

20:17.893 --> 20:19.275
Think I put all your organs
back in place.

20:19.375 --> 20:20.556
Thank you.
How do you feel?

20:20.656 --> 20:22.477
Good.

20:22.577 --> 20:25.560
Do you feel like
I'm maybe missing something?

20:25.660 --> 20:28.202
Oh.

20:28.302 --> 20:29.844
Aw, man.
What is this?

20:29.944 --> 20:33.527
I mean, it's probably not vital,
right?

20:33.627 --> 20:35.368
I feel fine.
I guess I'll just leave it.

20:35.468 --> 20:37.470
Yeah.
[ Wet splat ]
